definition:
A man living at the time of the Patriarchs, first mentioned at Gen.36.26; 
 son of: Dishon (H1787); 
 brother of: Hemdan (H2533), Eshban (H0790) and Cheran (H3763)
 § Ithran = "advantage"
1) an Edomite, son of Dishon, a Horite, and probably a phylarch of a tribe of the Horim
2) an descendant of Asher
